Spell Checker class. Provides functionality to check the spelling of words in a text file and suggesting alternatives to misspelled words.

checkWord

private boolean checkWord(java.lang.String word,
                          java.lang.Object[] results)
Spell checks a specified word. If the word is found in the dictionary, returns true. Otherwise, tries to find alternatives to the word by adding and removing one character at all positions within the word and swapping adjacent characters in the word. The list of these alternatives which are in the dictionary is returned to the caller in the array 'results', which is a Set collection.

Parameters:
word - The word to be checked.
results - A one item array to Set of advices
Returns:
True if the original word is found in the dictionary.

checkOneCharacterAdded

private void checkOneCharacterAdded(java.lang.String word,
                                    java.lang.Object[] results)
Takes a word, and generates a list of words by adding each alphabet character one by one to all of the positions within the word, but only one character at a time. For all of these new words, makes a check in the dictionary. If a word exists in the dictionary, this word is added to the set of results.

Parameters:
word - The word to be checked
results - The one item array of Set of new words that exist in the dictionary.
